<td class="navbox-group" style=";;">Theorists-<a href="/wiki/Developmental_stage_theories" title="Developmental stage theories">theories</a></td>
<td style="text-align:left;border-left:2px solid #fdfdfd;width:100%;padding:0px;;;" class="navbox-list navbox-odd">
<div style="padding:0em 0.25em"><a href="/wiki/John_Bowlby" title="John Bowlby">John Bowlby</a>-<a href="/wiki/Attachment_theory" title="Attachment theory">attachment</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Urie_Bronfenbrenner" title="Urie Bronfenbrenner">Urie Bronfenbrenner</a>-<a href="/wiki/Ecological_Systems_Theory" title="Ecological Systems Theory">ecological systems</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Erik_Erikson" title="Erik Erikson">Erik Erikson</a>-<a href="/wiki/Psychosocial_development" title="Psychosocial development">psychosocial</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Sigmund_Freud" title="Sigmund Freud">Sigmund Freud</a>-<a href="/wiki/Psychosexual_development" title="Psychosexual development">psychosexual</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Lawrence_Kohlberg" title="Lawrence Kohlberg">Lawrence Kohlberg</a>-<a href="/wiki/Kohlberg%27s_stages_of_moral_development" title="Kohlberg's stages of moral development">moral</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Jean_Piaget" title="Jean Piaget">Jean Piaget</a>-<strong class="selflink">cognitive</strong><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Lev_Vygotsky" title="Lev Vygotsky">Lev Vygotsky</a>-<a href="/wiki/Cultural-historical_psychology" title="Cultural-historical psychology">cultural-historical</a></div>
